3. State Machine — Session Lifecycle

Where it applies:
End-to-end session control (client → pivot → host → return)

Purpose:
Control execution order and prevent invalid transitions.

Template:

from enum import Enum, auto
class SessionState(Enum):
    INIT = auto()
    VALIDATING = auto()
    ENCRYPTING = auto()
    STORING = auto()
    COMPLETE = auto()
    FAILED = auto()
class Session:
    def __init__(self):
        self.state = SessionState.INIT
    def transition(self, new_state):
        valid = {
            SessionState.INIT: [SessionState.VALIDATING],
            SessionState.VALIDATING: [SessionState.ENCRYPTING, SessionState.FAILED],
            SessionState.ENCRYPTING: [SessionState.STORING],
            SessionState.STORING: [SessionState.COMPLETE],
        }
        if new_state in valid.get(self.state, []):
            self.state = new_state
        else:
            raise Exception(f"Invalid transition: {self.state} → {new_state}")

